# strategies/

Drop `.qkt` files in this directory. They're mounted into the running daemon at
`/strategies` (read-only).

Bybit symbols use the prefix `BYBIT_SPOT:` (spot trading) or `BYBIT_PERP:` (linear
perpetual futures). Examples:

```
SYMBOLS
    btc = BYBIT_PERP:BTCUSDT EVERY 5m WARMUP 50 BARS
    eth = BYBIT_SPOT:ETHUSDT EVERY 1m WARMUP 21 BARS
```

To deploy one:

```bash
make deploy STRAT=ema_cross
```

That runs `qkt deploy /strategies/ema_cross.qkt --as ema_cross` inside the
container. The daemon registers it and starts evaluating rules on the next tick.

To stop one:

```bash
make stop STRAT=ema_cross
```

By default the compose file points qkt at Bybit testnet — flip `BYBIT_TESTNET=false`
in `.env` and restart with `make up` when you're ready for mainnet.

